\p{Mr. Ziegel's existing oscilloscope and available Saleae Logic Pro 8 (via Tufts) save $928 off the original estimate. Mr. Ziegel has extensive personal experience with Saleae for embedded firmware debugging (GDB, Cutter, protocol analysis across SPI/I2C/UART/CAN), making the logic analyzer immediately productive for Cyton and Uncut Gem debugging without ramp-up time.}
\p{For context: this entire lab at $3,801 costs less than a single PLUX fNIRS Pioneer Kit (\ref{bcf-0011}) and enables Mr. Ziegel to design, print, assemble, debug, and validate every BCI device in the horse inventory in-house. The kscale-biomimetic-supply skill's tariff analysis reinforces this: domestic fabrication capability eliminates dependency on overseas manufacturing for every iteration cycle.}
}
